Overall Experience:
The combination of cleanliness and swift service makes the KFC on Streatham High Street a reliable choice for a quick meal. text:
I came here twice when I was working locally. Easy choice for a lunch. The store is pretty small and all the chats was left upside down on the tables as if they were mopping up the floor for preparing closing. On my first visit, I walked straight to the till as I wanted to pay cash. One of the workers made eye contact with me, but didn’t say a word and carried on doing what he was doing (fiddling with things to make himself look busy). I waited 10 minutes before I decided to make my order on the kiosk and pay by card. The food then came out really quick.

On my second visit, the kiosk wasn’t working, so I walked right upto the till, and the lovely lady served me with good customer service skills. She was amazing, and answered a couple questions I had about the food on the menu.

The reason why I still give them a one star review is because the food was pretty much cold when I got back onsite to eat my lunch. I was only 3mins walk away, and on both occasions my food was pretty cold. address: 116 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Michael Hu
text:
Used to go there whenever I don't have time to cook at home and don't want to think about what to eat. Most staff were professional and friendly.

However, the food tastes worse than before IMHO. The chicken nuggets were so salty that I had to drink more water after eating them. While everyone knows KFC and its counterparts are nowhere near healthy food choices, as one of the world's largest fast food chains, you can do better - by offering less salt and sugar, and  providing fresher meat and everything else.

If it's a takeaway order, do check everything in your bag before you leave, as I have found more than twice that they may forget something in your order, be it a bottle of water or whatever.

The in-store hygiene can be better.

address: 116 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1BW, United Kingdom
name: Jack Morris
text:
Service was abysmal.

The woman who served me could not speak English very well. To make it clear this has absolutely nothing to do with race but not being able to speak the language really made it a frustrating transaction by the end.

It took 10-15 minutes to complete a simple order and pay before even waiting for my food.  Many items were done incorrectly and had to be changed several times as she both couldn't understand me and didn't know how to work the machine correctly. She grew very angry with me because I kept having to tell her she was inputting the wrong things and correcting her. She stormed off to get another member of staff who translated for her.

She chased me out of the shop to give me an item (fries) she had forgotten. I should have stopped and checked my order right there but I was stupid and when I got home i realised I still had an incorrect order.

I would recommend going to a different local KFC or even paying for delivery from another KFC as the time wasted, rudeness, frustration and wrong order were not worth it.
